        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 28 at 3:40AM CDT by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI</headline>
        <description>At 340 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Monroe, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Monroe, Newark, Brodhead, Juda, Avon, Magnolia, Orfordville,
Evansville, Albany, and Footville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
